org.eclipse.keyple.example.pc.calypso

Class Demo_HoplinkTransaction

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.eclipse.keyple.example.pc.calypso.Demo_HoplinkTransaction
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.eclipse.keyple.seproxy.event.ObservableReader.ReaderObserver, org.eclipse.keyple.util.Observable.Observer<org.eclipse.keyple.seproxy.event.ReaderEvent>

    public class Demo_HoplinkTransaction
extends java.lang.Object
implements org.eclipse.keyple.seproxy.event.ObservableReader.ReaderObserver
    This Calypso demonstration code consists in:
    1. Setting up a two-reader configuration (main) and adding an observer method (update)
    2. Starting a card operation when a PO presence is notified (operatePoTransactions)
    3. Opening a logical channel with the CSM (C1 CSM is expected) see (CSM_C1_ATR_REGEX)
    4. Attempting to open a logical channel with the PO with 3 options:
      • Selection with a fake AID
      • Selection with a Navigo AID
      • Selection with a Hoplink AID
    5. Display SeRequest/SeResponse data (printSelectAppResponseStatus)
    6. If the Hoplink selection succeeded, do 3 Hoplink transactions (operateMultipleHoplinkTransactions).

    The Hoplink transactions demonstrated here illustrate the 2 and 3-step modes and also show the logical channel management.

    Read the doc of each methods for further details.

      • operateMultipleHoplinkTransactions

        public void operateMultipleHoplinkTransactions(org.eclipse.keyple.calypso.transaction.PoSecureSession poTransaction,
                                               org.eclipse.keyple.seproxy.ApduResponse fciData)
                                        throws org.eclipse.keyple.seproxy.exception.IOReaderException
        Chain 3 Hoplink transactions: 2-step, 3-step, 2-step (see @link doHoplinkTwoStepAuthentication and @link doHoplinkThreeStepReadWriteTransaction)

        To illustrate the the logical channel management, it is kept open after the 1st transaction.

        Closed after the end of the 2nd transaction and reopened before the 3rd transaction.

        Finally the logical channel is closed at the end of the 3rd transaction.

        Parameters:
        poTransaction - PoSecureSession object
        fciData - FCI data from the selection step
        Throws:
        org.eclipse.keyple.seproxy.exception.IOReaderException - reader exception (defined as public for purposes of javadoc)
